<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<!-- When creating a new activity, make a copy of this file with appropriate name -->
<worksheet xml:id="">
  <title>Average Rate of Change (Application)</title>

  <!-- Optional introduction -->
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Solve the following average rate of change application problems.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Jojo has a business selling mood rings (they'll be making a comeback!).  Jojo's data analyst claims that if Jojo sells a box of mood rings for a price $<m>p</m>, then they will be able to sell <m>d(p) = p^2-100p+2400</m> boxes of mood rings when <m>p</m> has a value between $0 and $40.
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Determine the average rate of change of the number of boxes between the prices $10 and $30.  Make sure to include units in your answer.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              What does the number you determined in (a) tell you about what will happen if Jojo changes their price?  Be as specific as you can.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              What are the domain and range of the.function?
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Jojo has been suffering from stress because of the pressure of the mood ring business.  Jojo now wears a device that measures blood pressure every 10 minutes.  Here are the readings of systolic pressure (i.e. the upper number in blood pressure) measured in millimeters of mercury (mmHg).
      </p>
      <tabular halign="right">
        <row>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">Time (minutes)</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"><m>0</m></cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">10</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">20</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">30</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">40</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor" right="minor">50</cell>
          <cell bottom="minor">60</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell right="minor">BP (mmHg)</cell>
          <cell right="minor"><m>105</m></cell>
          <cell right="minor">112</cell>
          <cell right="minor">116</cell>
          <cell right="minor">122</cell>
          <cell right="minor">125</cell>
          <cell right="minor">129</cell>
          <cell>135</cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              What is the average rate of change of blood pressure with respect to time between the beginning and end of the readings? Include units.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              What does the number you computed above tell you about Jojo's blood pressure.  Be as specific as possible.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Based on the number you computed in (a), what do you expect Jojo's blood pressure to be after 68 minutes?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Based on the number you computed in (a), when would you expect Jojo's blood pressure to reach 150 mmHg?
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

</worksheet>